[2]Georgia
Date: 18 Feb 2010
Source: News Jacksonville.com [edited]
<http://jacksonville.com/news/georgia/2010-02-18/story/rabies_warning_issued_in_camden_county>


Rabies warning issued in Camden County
--------------------------------------
Health officials are urging St. Marys, Georgia, residents to take
precautions after a stray cat found 11 Feb 2010 in the Forest Mission
area tested positive for rabies. Residents should avoid contact with
wild or stray animals, watch for unusual behavior in pets and
wildlife, and keep all pet vaccinations up to date to protect them
against the potentially deadly virus.

Officials with the Coastal Health District have recommended the
following precautions:

- Do not handle, feed or unintentionally attract wild animals with
open garbage cans or by leaving pet food out overnight.

- Never adopt wild animals, or try to nurse sick animals to health or
bring them into your home. Call animal control or an animal rescue
agency for help.

- Teach children to never handle unfamiliar animals, wild or domestic,
even if they appear friendly.

- Call your local animal control agency to report any animals showing
suspicious behavior.

- If bitten by an animal, seek medical care immediately and contact
animal control officials.

