[Pets should be vaccinated against this deadly disease whether or not
there is an outbreak of the disease.

While these articles remind owners of cats, dogs and ferrets to
vaccinate, the same is true for livestock owners. Rabid raccoons can
also bite horses or cows. Vaccination of your animals is cheap
insurance compared to a bite that can cost a human life. - Mod.TG]

